LSE-listed mineral sands miner Kenmare Resources paid $15.41-million to the government of Mozambique as part of its tax, royalties and fees payments for 2021. Kenmare operates the Moma titanium minerals mine, on the north-east coast of Mozambique. It contains deposits of heavy minerals, including titanium minerals ilmenite and rutile, as well as the zirconium silicate mineral, zircon. Of the total, $6.16-million comprised taxes, $8.86-million royalties and $388 000 fees. The portion attributed to Kenmare Moma Mining is $10.74-million, of which $6.16-million is taxes and $4.2-million royalties, while $388 000 comprised fees. Kenmare Moma Processing’s portion comprised $4.66-million in royalties.